4 There stood Minos horribly, and growls:
5 he examines the sins at the entrance;
6 he judges and sends according to how it coils.

7 I say that when the badly born soul
8 comes before [it], it confesses all;
9 and that knower of the sins

10 sees what place of hell is from it;
11 it coils with the tail so many times
12 however many degrees it wants to be put down.

13 Always before him many stand;
14 they go to each other to the judgment,
15 they say and hear and then are turned down.

31 The infernal storm, which never rests,
32 leads the spirits with its rapine;
33 turning and striking, it harasses them.

34 When they arrive before the ruin,
35 there are the shrieks, the weeping, the lament;
36 they blaspheme there against divine virtue.

61 The other is she who killed herself in love,
62 and broke faith to the ashes of Sychaeus;
63 then is Cleopatra lustful.

